rComments: Professor Tafarodi is one of the best teachers I've ever had in my life. There are definitely many readings to do but you don't have to learn everything by heart in order to pass, what matters is understanding the concepts. You'll get out of this course so much more culturally enriched too!

rComments: If you're bad at writing, I would not take this course. Literally all the marks are based on essays (you have to write 3 essays per test, and then a 15-page assignment worth 40%). Also, readings are 100+ tedious pages from TWO textbooks that are mandatory. Nice prof, but extremely verbose and takes a while to get to the point in lectures.

Is hands-down one of my favourite professors on campus. I hold a lot of respect for his teaching methods and interest in students. An inspiriing professor who genuinely cares about the topics he lectures and the undergraduate experience of his students.
